Java enum: Constant examples
Because a Java enum type is good for defining a fixed set of constants, itâ€™s often used to represent constants like these in Java programs:

Days of the week
Months in the year
Cards in a deck
Directions (north, south, east, west)
Menu item options
Defining arguments for a command-line program
States in the United States (such as for a drop-down list)

public enum Day
{
  SUNDAY, MONDAY, TUESDAY, WEDNESDAY, THURSDAY, FRIDAY, SATURDAY 
}

public enum Month
{
  JANUARY, FEBRUARY, MARCH, APRIL, MAY, JUNE,
  JULY, AUGUST, SEPTEMBER, OCTOBER, NOVEMBER, DECEMBER
}

public enum Margin
{
  TOP, RIGHT, BOTTOM, LEFT
}